data.chText: 选择；挑选；选拔
data.enText: the process of choosing sb/sth from a group of people or things, usually according to a system

data.chText: 明天将确定队伍的最后人选。
data.enText: The final team selection will be made tomorrow.

data.chText: 号码的随机抽取
data.enText: the random selection of numbers

data.chText: 挑选标准
data.enText: selection criteria

data.chText: 选拔过程
data.enText: the selection process

data.chText: 被挑选的人（或物）；被选中者；入选者
data.enText: a number of people or things that have been chosen from a larger group

data.chText: 下面选登了部分读者的意见。
data.enText: A selection of readers' comments are published below.

data.chText: 可供选择的事物
data.enText: a collection of things from which sth can be chosen

data.chText: 展厅里有多种式样的厨房可供选择。
data.enText: The showroom has a wide selection of kitchens.

data.chText: 以上各词均指选中或特别喜爱的人或事物。
data.enText: These are all words for a person or thing that is chosen, or that is liked more than others.
choice

data.chText: 指入选者、选中的东西：
data.enText: a person or thing that is chosen

data.chText: 她是这个职位当然的人选。
data.enText: She's the obvious choice for the job.
favourite/favorite

data.chText: 指同类人或事物中最喜欢的一个：
data.enText: a person or thing that you like more than the others of the same type

data.chText: 你最喜欢哪一个？
data.enText: Which one's your favourite?
preference

data.chText: 指偏爱的或最喜爱的事物：
data.enText: a thing that is liked better or best

data.chText: 人的爱好和选择各不相同。
data.enText: Tastes and preferences vary from individual to individual.

data.chText: 用favourite还是preference？
favourite指最喜欢因而常有、常做或常听等的事物；preference指在可以选择的情况下会较喜欢有或做的事物。
data.enText: Your favourites are the things you like best, and that you have, do, listen to, etc. often; your preferences are the things that you would rather have or do if you can choose.
favourite or preference?
selection

data.chText: 指从大的群中选出来的一组人或物：
data.enText: a number of people or things that have been chosen from a larger group

data.chText: 下面选登了部分读者评论。
data.enText: A selection of reader's comments are published below.
pick

data.chText: 指选中的人或物：
data.enText: ( rather informal , especially NAmE ) a person or thing that is chosen

data.chText: 她是他认为最好的女演员。
data.enText: She was his pick for best actress.
sb's choice/favourite/preference/pick for sth
sb's choice/selection/pick as sth
an obvious choice/favourite/selection
a(n) excellent/good/popular/fine choice/selection

tr: the act of choosing or selecting
example: your choice of colors was unfortunate

tr: the person or thing chosen or selected
example: he was my pick for mayor

tr: a passage selected from a larger work
example: he presented excerpts from William James' philosophical writings

tr: an assortment of things from which a choice can be made
example: the store carried a large selection of shoes

tr: a natural process resulting in the evolution of organisms best adapted to the environment

value.def: Selection is the act of selecting one or more people or things from a group.

example.tran: 达尔文的自然选择理论

example.ex: Dr. Sullivan's selection to head the Department of Health was greeted with satisfaction...
example.tran: 人们对沙利文博士当选卫生部部长表示满意。

example.ex: The children have to sit a tough selection test.
example.tran: 孩子们必须参加一次严格的选拔测试。

value.def: A selection of people or things is a set of them that have been selected from a larger group.

example.ex: ...a dramatic rendition of selections from Dickens' A Christmas Carol.
example.tran: 以戏剧形式演绎的狄更斯《圣诞颂歌》节选片段

value.tran: 挑选出来的一批人(或事物)

value.def: The selection of goods in a shop is the particular range of goods that it has available and from which you can choose what you want.

example.ex: It offers the widest selection of antiques of every description in a one day market.
example.tran: 它在为期一天的集市上出售应有尽有的各种古董。

value.tran: (商店内)可供挑选的某类商品
